1
00:00:01.335 --> 00:00:04.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rock 'n' roll playing]

2
00:00:04.213 --> 00:00:06.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[buzz of conversation]

3
00:00:09.343 --> 00:00:11.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now these are delicious.

4
00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:16.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Uh, leave some for the rest of us.
-Hey, I'm eating for two.

5
00:00:18.352 --> 00:00:19.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Great party, Neelix.

6
00:00:20.521 --> 00:00:22.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everybody seems to be enjoying it.

7
00:00:22.898 --> 00:00:24.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, except the Doc.

8
00:00:29.530 --> 00:00:31.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those are for eating,
not scanning.

9
00:00:31.573 --> 00:00:32.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What exactly are they?

10
00:00:32.908 --> 00:00:36.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Cheese pierogies.
Zefram Cochrane's favorite.

11
00:00:36.161 --> 00:00:38.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They have absolutely
no nutritional value.

12
00:00:38.539 --> 00:00:39.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
This is a party, Doctor.

13
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sometimes you have to forget
about nutrition.

14
00:00:42.918 --> 00:00:45.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could include a vitamin supplement
when you replicate.

15
00:00:45.587 --> 00:00:48.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Replicate?
I made them myself.

16
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:51.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You two have outdone yourselves.

17
00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:54.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've never seen First Contact Day
celebrated quite like this.

18
00:00:54.972 --> 00:00:57.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I was your age, all it meant
was a day off from school.

19
00:00:57.975 --> 00:01:00.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Neelix and I thought
we should make it more fun.

20
00:01:00.561 --> 00:01:02.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you certainly succeeded.

21
00:01:02.354 --> 00:01:05.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When is Commander Tuvok
making his presentation?

22
00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:07.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, now's as good a time as any.

23
00:01:07.234 --> 00:01:08.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain.

24
00:01:09.570 --> 00:01:12.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, may I have everyone's
attention, please?

25
00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:17.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[music stops]
-In honor of the 315th anniversary

26
00:01:17.828 --> 00:01:20.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of his ancestors' arrival on Earth,

27
00:01:20.622 --> 00:01:23.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've asked Mr. Tuvok
to recite the first words

28
00:01:24.001 --> 00:01:26.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
spoken to humans by a Vulcan.

29
00:01:26.670 --> 00:01:27.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander?

30
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:30.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is this really necessary?

31
00:01:31.383 --> 00:01:32.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You promised.

32
00:01:34.052 --> 00:01:35.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very well.

33
00:01:36.722 --> 00:01:38.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Live long and prosper.

34
00:01:38.557 --> 00:01:40.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[man] Ah.
-[applause]

35
00:01:42.769 --> 00:01:47.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And now, for some more
of Zefram Cochrane's favorite music.

36
00:01:47.274 --> 00:01:49.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rock 'n' roll playing]

37
00:01:49.651 --> 00:01:51.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[quiet chatter]

38
00:01:55.741 --> 00:01:57.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

39
00:01:57.576 --> 00:01:58.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughter]

40
00:01:59.161 --> 00:02:01.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, come on, Mr. Vulcan.

41
00:02:02.372 --> 00:02:03.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Vulcans do not dance.

42
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:05.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But it's tradition.

43
00:02:06.084 --> 00:02:08.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There is no tradition, Mr. Neelix.

44
00:02:08.211 --> 00:02:10.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This ceremony
is entirely your invention.

45
00:02:10.797 --> 00:02:13.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is an official
ship function, Commander.

46
00:02:13.258 --> 00:02:16.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't make me order you to dance.

47
00:02:16.345 --> 00:02:19.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry to interrupt, but I've got
some interesting news.

48
00:02:19.181 --> 00:02:20.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix, you might want to hear this.

49
00:02:20.641 --> 00:02:21.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

50
00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:26.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Long-range sensors have detected
several hundred life signs

51
00:02:26.938 --> 00:02:29.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
approximately 4.9 light-years away.

52
00:02:30.734 --> 00:02:31.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're Talaxian.

53
00:04:34.232 --> 00:04:36.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-Are we there yet?
-Not exactly.

54
00:04:36.526 --> 00:04:40.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
The life signs appear to be coming
from inside that asteroid field.

55
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Neelix]
From a ship?

56
00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We are not detecting any vessels.

57
00:04:44.618 --> 00:04:47.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-No response from hails?
-Not yet.

58
00:04:48.747 --> 00:04:50.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I hope they're all right.

59
00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:52.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
There's a lot of interference.

60
00:04:52.626 --> 00:04:54.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Maybe they haven't received
our transmissions.

61
00:04:54.628 --> 00:04:56.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Can we move in any closer?

62
00:04:56.463 --> 00:04:59.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Voyager</i> is too big
to maneuver safely in there.

63
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:01.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We could take the <i>Flyer.</i>

64
00:05:04.221 --> 00:05:06.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It wouldn't have hurt you
to do a few steps.

65
00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:08.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I am trying to concentrate
on the shields, Mr. Neelix.

66
00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I think you were just afraid.

67
00:05:10.644 --> 00:05:13.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-That's absurd.
-It's understandable.

68
00:05:13.605 --> 00:05:17.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-There were a lot of people watching.
-Vulcans don't experience fear.

69
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm going to make it
my personal mission

70
00:05:20.821 --> 00:05:23.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
to get you to dance at least once
before we reach Earth.

71
00:05:23.907 --> 00:05:26.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Then I suggest you find
a more productive hobby.

72
00:05:26.618 --> 00:05:27.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If you two don't stop it,

73
00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:29.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm going to come back there
and separate you.

74
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:32.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[console beeping]

75
00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:37.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've localized the life signs.
Bearing 108, mark 26.

76
00:05:37.879 --> 00:05:40.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They appear to be inside
a large asteroid.

77
00:05:40.549 --> 00:05:42.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-Inside?
-[rumbling]

78
00:05:42.759 --> 00:05:45.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-What was that?
-A thermalyte explosive.

79
00:05:45.512 --> 00:05:47.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
30.6 kilometers to port.

80
00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:50.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm detecting another projectile,
heading directly toward us.

81
00:05:50.725 --> 00:05:52.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Evasive maneuvers.

82
00:05:57.941 --> 00:05:58.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've lost shields.

83
00:06:00.026 --> 00:06:01.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Main propulsion is off-line.

84
00:06:01.862 --> 00:06:03.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're going to have
to make an emergency landing.

85
00:06:04.072 --> 00:06:05.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where?

86
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:07.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Talaxians' asteroid
is the closest.

87
00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:10.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The surface is covered
with craters, ice fields.

88
00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:14.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
We don't have a choice.

89
00:06:14.373 --> 00:06:15.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hold on.

90
00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:40.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Problem?

91
00:06:40.901 --> 00:06:42.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've lost contact
with the away team.

92
00:06:42.986 --> 00:06:46.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I also detected some unusual energy
discharges in the asteroid field.

93
00:06:46.281 --> 00:06:47.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What kind of discharges?
-It's difficult to tell

94
00:06:48.158 --> 00:06:49.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
because of the interference,

95
00:06:49.910 --> 00:06:52.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but they appear
to be thermalytic explosions.

96
00:06:52.203 --> 00:06:55.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe several of them
were in close proximity to the <i>Flyer.</i>

97
00:06:55.999 --> 00:06:57.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Source?

98
00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:58.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Unknown.

99
00:07:00.712 --> 00:07:03.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
We'll need to send a rescue team.

100
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:05.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Work with B'Elanna.
Try to modify the shields

101
00:07:05.926 --> 00:07:08.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on one of the shuttles
to withstand these explosions.

102
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stay still.

103
00:07:21.691 --> 00:07:23.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't worry.
It's not serious.

104
00:07:25.862 --> 00:07:27.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Am I inside the asteroid?

105
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:29.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

106
00:07:29.199 --> 00:07:30.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is my home.

107
00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:32.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where are my friends?

108
00:07:32.744 --> 00:07:36.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you mean the aliens who were
on the ship with you, they're safe.

109
00:07:38.541 --> 00:07:39.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to see them.

110
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You need to rest.

111
00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:48.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What were you doing
in the asteroid field?

112
00:07:51.054 --> 00:07:52.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Looking for you.

113
00:07:53.223 --> 00:07:56.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, not you specifically,

114
00:07:57.060 --> 00:08:00.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but my ship detected Talaxians.

115
00:08:00.605 --> 00:08:02.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't come across any in years, so...

116
00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:05.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

117
00:08:05.819 --> 00:08:08.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm Neelix.

118
00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:09.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dexa.

119
00:08:09.781 --> 00:08:11.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I had an uncle named Neelix.

120
00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:16.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are there other Talaxians
on your ship?

121
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm the only one.

122
00:08:18.456 --> 00:08:20.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why are you living with aliens?

123
00:08:21.001 --> 00:08:22.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're my friends.

124
00:08:23.670 --> 00:08:25.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did you receive our hails?

125
00:08:25.714 --> 00:08:26.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

126
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:28.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why didn't you respond?

127
00:08:28.550 --> 00:08:30.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We avoid contact with outsiders.

128
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:34.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We were attacked.

129
00:08:35.974 --> 00:08:37.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There were explosions.

130
00:08:39.144 --> 00:08:41.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Did you...?
-No.

131
00:08:41.271 --> 00:08:42.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're not violent.

132
00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:44.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who fired at us?

133
00:08:44.691 --> 00:08:46.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No one fired at you.

134
00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:48.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are miners
who use explosive charges

135
00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:50.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to break apart the asteroids,

136
00:08:50.405 --> 00:08:52.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so they can collect minerals
from the debris.

137
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:55.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish we'd known.

138
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:56.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why were you carrying weapons?

139
00:08:57.871 --> 00:09:00.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's standard procedure
for an away mission.

140
00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:06.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello. What's your name?

141
00:09:06.421 --> 00:09:08.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Brax. What's yours?

142
00:09:08.965 --> 00:09:10.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I told you not to come in here.

143
00:09:10.967 --> 00:09:12.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just wanted to see him.

144
00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:15.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're supposed to be helping Oxilon.

145
00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:17.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He doesn't look dangerous to me.

146
00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:23.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you have the wrong idea
about us.

147
00:09:23.271 --> 00:09:25.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not supposed to be
talking to you at all.

148
00:09:27.901 --> 00:09:29.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm feeling better.

149
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to see my friends now.

150
00:09:34.282 --> 00:09:37.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-I've been told not to let you leave.

151
00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:51.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Harry?

152
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:52.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Still no response to hails.

153
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.886 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Janeway to the Shuttle Bay.
-[Seven]<i> Go ahead, Captain.</i>

154
00:09:55.053 --> 00:09:57.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's the status
of the shield modifications?

155
00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:59.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Lieutenant Torres and I will be</i>
<i>finished in a few minutes.</i>

156
00:09:59.849 --> 00:10:02.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good. Take an away team
and find them.

157
00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:05.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[electronic beeping]

158
00:10:05.396 --> 00:10:07.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, there's a ship
approaching from astern.

159
00:10:07.774 --> 00:10:09.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're being hailed.

160
00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:10.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On screen.

161
00:10:12.070 --> 00:10:13.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Identify yourselves.</i>

162
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:16.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm Captain Janeway
of the Federation Starship<i> Voyager.</i>

163
00:10:17.867 --> 00:10:19.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Commander Nocona.</i>

164
00:10:19.244 --> 00:10:21.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is our asteroid field.</i>

165
00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We weren't aware of that.

166
00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:25.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Now you are.</i>

167
00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:29.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We lost one of our shuttles
inside the field.

168
00:10:29.546 --> 00:10:31.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're preparing
to send a rescue team.

169
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:34.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>All the resources belong to us.</i>

170
00:10:34.342 --> 00:10:35.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're not interested
in the resources.

171
00:10:35.760 --> 00:10:37.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were only trying
to make contact with the Talaxians.

172
00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:41.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What's your interest in them?</i>

173
00:10:41.266 --> 00:10:43.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One of my crewmen is from Talax.

174
00:10:43.476 --> 00:10:45.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was eager to meet some of his people.

175
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:49.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You should have requested permission</i>
<i>before sending in a shuttle.</i>

176
00:10:49.357 --> 00:10:51.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We have a mining operation in progress.</i>

177
00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:54.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does that explain
the explosions we detected?

178
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:56.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Mining charges.</i>

179
00:10:56.614 --> 00:10:59.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd appreciate it
if you'd stop using them,

180
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:00.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until we can get our people out.

181
00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:04.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm sorry.</i>
<i>We're on a strict deadline.</i>

182
00:11:04.747 --> 00:11:07.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But I'll conduct a search</i>
<i>for your crew.</i>

183
00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:10.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If they need help,</i>
<i>we'll provide it.</i>

184
00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:12.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's kind of you.

185
00:11:12.755 --> 00:11:15.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But we're prepared to go in
and get them ourselves.

186
00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:19.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I cannot guarantee your safety</i>
<i>if you enter the asteroid field.</i>

187
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:21.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Stay here.</i>

188
00:11:21.973 --> 00:11:24.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We'll contact you</i>
<i>when we find your people.</i>

189
00:11:37.363 --> 00:11:40.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think
you're supposed to be here.

190
00:11:40.158 --> 00:11:43.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is my home.
You can't tell me what to do.

191
00:11:43.494 --> 00:11:45.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, of course not.

192
00:11:45.955 --> 00:11:47.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just don't want you
to get in trouble.

193
00:11:48.917 --> 00:11:51.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that a model ship?

194
00:11:51.252 --> 00:11:53.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's it called?

195
00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:55.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How about the <i>Two-Tailed Talchok</i>?

196
00:11:57.634 --> 00:11:58.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The <i>Fur Fly</i>?

197
00:11:58.927 --> 00:12:00.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[giggles]

198
00:12:01.763 --> 00:12:03.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ship I come from
is called the <i>Voyager.</i>

199
00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:05.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is it big?

200
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:07.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And fast.

201
00:12:08.603 --> 00:12:10.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can I see it?

202
00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:13.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think it would be
a little difficult

203
00:12:13.358 --> 00:12:15.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to take you there
while I'm stuck here.

204
00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:18.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But if your mother
would let me out...

205
00:12:18.655 --> 00:12:20.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[door closing]
-That's her.

206
00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:22.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[whispers]
You'd better hide.

207
00:12:22.909 --> 00:12:24.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You won't tell her I'm here?

208
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, of course not.

209
00:12:35.672 --> 00:12:39.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix, this is Oxilon,
our council regent.

210
00:12:40.718 --> 00:12:42.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wish I could say
it was nice to meet you,

211
00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:44.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but this wasn't exactly
the welcome I was expecting.

212
00:12:45.139 --> 00:12:46.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're free to go now.

213
00:12:55.149 --> 00:12:56.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about my friends?

214
00:12:56.359 --> 00:12:58.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've determined
they aren't hostile.

215
00:12:58.861 --> 00:13:01.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They've been treated for their injuries
and asked to leave.

216
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:04.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're aboard your shuttle
making repairs.

217
00:13:04.575 --> 00:13:06.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll take you there.

218
00:13:06.995 --> 00:13:10.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, now that everything
has been cleared up,

219
00:13:10.957 --> 00:13:13.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
maybe we could talk...

220
00:13:14.002 --> 00:13:15.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
get to know each other a little?

221
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:20.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you'd like.

222
00:13:21.217 --> 00:13:22.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My friends, too?

223
00:13:23.136 --> 00:13:24.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

224
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:25.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not?

225
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:28.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've learned from experience
to keep to ourselves.

226
00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:33.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, if they're not welcome,
I'm not staying, either.

227
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:36.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's your choice.

228
00:13:43.781 --> 00:13:45.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know Oxilon seems overly cautious,

229
00:13:45.742 --> 00:13:47.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but we're not used to having visitors.

230
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:50.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many of you live here?

231
00:13:53.583 --> 00:13:55.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Close to 500.

232
00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All of our homes are connected
to the central cavern

233
00:13:57.879 --> 00:13:59.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
by tunnels and lifts.

234
00:13:59.672 --> 00:14:00.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They allow us to move easily

235
00:14:00.923 --> 00:14:03.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
from one section
of the asteroid to another.

236
00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:08.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It must have taken years
to build all of this.

237
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:10.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Almost five.

238
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:12.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It still isn't finished.

239
00:14:14.145 --> 00:14:16.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[male voice]<i> ...group five,</i>
<i>report to the lower level...</i>

240
00:14:16.522 --> 00:14:18.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did the technology come from?

241
00:14:18.733 --> 00:14:21.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We arrived here
with a caravan of six ships.

242
00:14:21.819 --> 00:14:25.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We disassembled all but one of them
and modified their components.

243
00:14:25.365 --> 00:14:27.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We converted torpedo launchers
to blast away rock

244
00:14:27.825 --> 00:14:29.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and excavate these tunnels.

245
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:32.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These conduits run
into the asteroid's core.

246
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:37.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We use geothermal energy to melt the ice
that covers most of the outer surface.

247
00:14:37.168 --> 00:14:39.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It provides us with oxygen and water.

248
00:14:40.129 --> 00:14:43.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who'd have imagined all of this
inside an asteroid?

249
00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:50.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your son seems like
a wonderful boy.

250
00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:54.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How would you know?
You only met him for a few seconds.

251
00:14:55.853 --> 00:14:59.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
True, but I'm a quick
judge of character.

252
00:15:00.650 --> 00:15:03.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He came to see you
while I was out, didn't he?

253
00:15:05.154 --> 00:15:07.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can't blame him
for being curious.

254
00:15:07.365 --> 00:15:10.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm. He's a lot like his father--

255
00:15:10.743 --> 00:15:12.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no fear.

256
00:15:12.662 --> 00:15:14.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to meet your husband.

257
00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:18.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's dead.

258
00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:21.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

259
00:15:21.462 --> 00:15:23.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I didn't mean to...
-It's... It's all right.

260
00:15:23.965 --> 00:15:25.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You didn't know.

261
00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:31.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix.

262
00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:34.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you all right?
-I'm fine.

263
00:15:34.976 --> 00:15:40.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dexa, this is Lieutenant Paris
and Commander Tuvok.

264
00:15:40.231 --> 00:15:43.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks for bringing him back.
We were getting worried.

265
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:47.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was nice to meet you.

266
00:15:56.664 --> 00:15:59.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what can I do to help?

267
00:16:00.126 --> 00:16:02.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you can give me a hand
with this plasma manifold.

268
00:16:05.339 --> 00:16:06.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did it go?

269
00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:10.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, uh, they didn't exactly
send out a welcoming committee,

270
00:16:10.636 --> 00:16:12.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I'm sure they have their reasons.

271
00:16:15.266 --> 00:16:17.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess my expectations
were a little high.

272
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:22.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I regret that you didn't have
a more fulfilling experience.

273
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:23.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's nice of you to say,
Commander,

274
00:16:23.816 --> 00:16:25.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it wasn't a complete
waste of time.

275
00:16:25.735 --> 00:16:27.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I got to meet some
of my people again...

276
00:16:27.862 --> 00:16:29.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
even if it was a short visit.

277
00:16:30.615 --> 00:16:31.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who knows?

278
00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:36.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's probably the last time
I'll ever see another Talaxian.

279
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:48.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good work.
Now we need to run a systems...

280
00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[beeping]
-[computer]<i> Intruder alert.</i>

281
00:16:51.093 --> 00:16:53.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At least we know internal sensors
are working.

282
00:17:04.524 --> 00:17:06.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

283
00:17:11.614 --> 00:17:12.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

284
00:17:12.949 --> 00:17:14.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Neelix]
Brax!

285
00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:19.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You know him?
-We're old friends.

286
00:17:20.331 --> 00:17:22.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You said you'd take me
to see<i> Voyager.</i>

287
00:17:22.416 --> 00:17:25.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't think your mother would approve.

288
00:17:26.170 --> 00:17:27.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You won't tell her
I was here, will you?

289
00:17:28.005 --> 00:17:29.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here?

290
00:17:29.924 --> 00:17:32.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

291
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:35.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

292
00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:40.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Oxilon] Three days isn't nearly
enough time for us

293
00:17:40.977 --> 00:17:42.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to dismantle all our equipment.

294
00:17:42.853 --> 00:17:45.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Nocona] You should have begun
the first time we asked.

295
00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:46.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can't wait any longer.

296
00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:48.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Demolition of the asteroid
is going to start

297
00:17:49.068 --> 00:17:50.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
whether you're here or not.

298
00:17:50.570 --> 00:17:51.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'd kill us?

299
00:17:52.863 --> 00:17:56.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We don't want to hurt anyone,
but our patience has run out.

300
00:17:56.701 --> 00:17:59.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've only got one ship.

301
00:17:59.161 --> 00:18:01.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There won't be enough room
for any of our belongings.

302
00:18:01.205 --> 00:18:04.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not our fault you took apart
your other vessels.

303
00:18:04.333 --> 00:18:06.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You can't do this.
-Dexa, don't provoke him.

304
00:18:07.128 --> 00:18:08.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where are we supposed to go?

305
00:18:08.879 --> 00:18:11.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sure you'll find a home somewhere.

306
00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:14.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is our home!

307
00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:15.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have no right to make us go.

308
00:18:16.804 --> 00:18:19.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[groans]
-Leave her alone!

309
00:18:22.393 --> 00:18:24.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bring him here!

310
00:18:25.605 --> 00:18:28.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Don't touch him!
-Are you going to stop me?

311
00:18:29.025 --> 00:18:30.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

312
00:18:31.360 --> 00:18:32.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

313
00:18:34.947 --> 00:18:35.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

314
00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:41.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've said what you've come to say,
and now I suggest you leave.

315
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:46.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have three days to evacuate.

316
00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:06.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can see now
why we're suspicious of outsiders.

317
00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:08.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you for protecting the boy...

318
00:19:09.190 --> 00:19:11.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'm afraid your actions
might make things worse.

319
00:19:11.859 --> 00:19:13.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How could they get any worse?

320
00:19:13.444 --> 00:19:16.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fighting back has never done anything
but cause us more trouble.

321
00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:18.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And what has running away
ever done for us?

322
00:19:18.658 --> 00:19:20.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's kept us alive.

323
00:19:20.451 --> 00:19:23.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe it's time we stayed
and defended ourselves.

324
00:19:23.287 --> 00:19:24.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will you help us?

325
00:19:26.749 --> 00:19:29.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I agree with Oxilon.
Fighting isn't the answer.

326
00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-But I'll try to help.
-How?

327
00:19:34.006 --> 00:19:37.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, uh...
we could talk to my captain.

328
00:19:37.301 --> 00:19:39.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe she can negotiate
with the miners,

329
00:19:39.929 --> 00:19:42.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
uh, get them to agree
to let you stay.

330
00:19:42.473 --> 00:19:44.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your captain would be willing to do that?

331
00:19:46.143 --> 00:19:48.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The best thing would be for you
to come to<i> Voyager--</i>

332
00:19:48.854 --> 00:19:50.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
talk to her yourself.

333
00:19:50.189 --> 00:19:53.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I want to go, too.
-Shh, Brax.

334
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:54.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don't you both come?

335
00:19:54.985 --> 00:19:58.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've seen your home.
I'd like you to see mine.

336
00:20:03.244 --> 00:20:05.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[doors open]

337
00:20:05.705 --> 00:20:07.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander Chakotay.

338
00:20:07.998 --> 00:20:11.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like you to meet Dexa...
and Brax.

339
00:20:11.502 --> 00:20:12.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome to the Bridge.

340
00:20:12.837 --> 00:20:14.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And this is Ensign Kim.

341
00:20:20.594 --> 00:20:21.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's this?

342
00:20:22.096 --> 00:20:24.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This... is an engineering station.

343
00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:27.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And over there is Tactical.

344
00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:30.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And down there is the Helm.

345
00:20:30.521 --> 00:20:34.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And this...
is the Captain's chair.

346
00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:37.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which station is yours?

347
00:20:37.445 --> 00:20:40.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, actually, I don't have a specific...
See, I'm-I'm more of a, uh...

348
00:20:40.906 --> 00:20:43.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix does too many things
to have just one station.

349
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:48.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's our ambassador,
morale officer, trade negotiator.

350
00:20:48.748 --> 00:20:51.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Without a doubt, he's the most
versatile member of our crew.

351
00:20:53.919 --> 00:20:55.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

352
00:20:55.713 --> 00:20:58.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Seven] As you can see,
our sensors are extremely precise.

353
00:20:59.049 --> 00:21:01.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can scan for life signs
light-years away.

354
00:21:01.635 --> 00:21:03.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's how we found you.

355
00:21:03.721 --> 00:21:05.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have something else
that may interest you.

356
00:21:09.602 --> 00:21:12.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What is it?
-Talax.

357
00:21:13.063 --> 00:21:15.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can scan that far away?

358
00:21:15.191 --> 00:21:17.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, this image is from our database.

359
00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:20.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's as beautiful as I remember.

360
00:21:22.281 --> 00:21:24.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's the Godo Mountain Range.

361
00:21:24.700 --> 00:21:26.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And the Axiana Lakes.

362
00:21:26.702 --> 00:21:28.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That was always one
of my favorite places.

363
00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:30.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mine, too.

364
00:21:32.082 --> 00:21:35.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't we just go back to Talax?
We could live there.

365
00:21:35.753 --> 00:21:38.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's still controlled by the Haakonians.

366
00:21:38.964 --> 00:21:42.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They don't treat Talaxians very well.
That's why we left.

367
00:21:42.176 --> 00:21:45.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe Neelix could go with us,
and we could fight them.

368
00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:47.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take the planet back.

369
00:21:48.349 --> 00:21:51.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If tomorrow's negotiations go well,
you won't have to go anywhere.

370
00:21:56.607 --> 00:21:59.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Next stop... Engineering.

371
00:21:59.276 --> 00:22:00.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The warp core!

372
00:22:01.904 --> 00:22:03.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix!

373
00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:04.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Naomi.

374
00:22:04.615 --> 00:22:07.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry. I forgot all about
our Kadis-Kot game.

375
00:22:08.035 --> 00:22:10.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's all right.
I know you're busy.

376
00:22:10.538 --> 00:22:11.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just want to meet your friends.

377
00:22:12.164 --> 00:22:14.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course. Dexa, Brax...

378
00:22:14.416 --> 00:22:16.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this is my goddaughter, Naomi.

379
00:22:16.377 --> 00:22:17.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hi.

380
00:22:17.545 --> 00:22:20.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You live on a beautiful ship.
-Thanks.

381
00:22:20.798 --> 00:22:23.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe Brax would like to go
to the holodeck.

382
00:22:23.259 --> 00:22:26.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-That's a great idea.
-Lieutenant Paris has a new program.

383
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:28.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Invaders from the Ninth Dimension."

384
00:22:28.264 --> 00:22:31.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Sounds scary.
-Very.

385
00:22:31.183 --> 00:22:32.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's a holodeck?

386
00:22:33.686 --> 00:22:36.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix is right.
Might be too scary for you.

387
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:39.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not afraid. Can I?

388
00:22:46.156 --> 00:22:48.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're lucky to have found these people.

389
00:22:51.495 --> 00:22:53.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They obviously think
a great deal of you.

390
00:22:53.873 --> 00:22:55.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The feeling's mutual.

391
00:23:08.596 --> 00:23:10.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To the Axiana Lakes.

392
00:23:16.353 --> 00:23:18.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It really is delicious.

393
00:23:18.564 --> 00:23:20.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've been saving it for 15 years.

394
00:23:21.108 --> 00:23:23.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wasn't sure I'd ever open it.

395
00:23:26.614 --> 00:23:27.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But tonight...

396
00:23:28.032 --> 00:23:30.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
seemed like the right occasion.

397
00:23:35.539 --> 00:23:37.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Would you like some more...

398
00:23:37.541 --> 00:23:38.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
taga cake?

399
00:23:38.709 --> 00:23:41.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A little, please.

400
00:23:42.713 --> 00:23:44.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't had this in years.

401
00:23:46.008 --> 00:23:47.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad you like it.

402
00:23:47.343 --> 00:23:49.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Mmm.
-It's a family recipe.

403
00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:51.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're a good cook.

404
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:56.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I haven't seen Brax this happy
since his father was alive.

405
00:23:59.271 --> 00:24:00.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did he...?

406
00:24:01.398 --> 00:24:04.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry. You probably
don't want to talk about it.

407
00:24:04.568 --> 00:24:06.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't mind.

408
00:24:07.696 --> 00:24:10.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd settled on a planet
called Phanos.

409
00:24:10.448 --> 00:24:12.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There was a lot
of unoccupied territory,

410
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:15.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the government restricted us
to a very small area.

411
00:24:15.245 --> 00:24:18.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why?
-They said it was a quarantine,

412
00:24:18.456 --> 00:24:20.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to protect the population
from alien diseases.

413
00:24:21.919 --> 00:24:23.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But it was just an excuse.

414
00:24:23.587 --> 00:24:27.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were outsiders. They didn't want us
mixing with their people.

415
00:24:29.218 --> 00:24:31.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It wasn't long before we realized
we didn't have enough land

416
00:24:32.096 --> 00:24:34.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to grow what we needed
to feed ourselves.

417
00:24:35.933 --> 00:24:40.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oxilon said we'd just have
to conserve our resources.

418
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:45.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But my husband was tired
of being told what to do.

419
00:24:45.526 --> 00:24:49.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, he started farming
outside the restricted zone.

420
00:24:50.072 --> 00:24:51.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They didn't like that.

421
00:24:51.448 --> 00:24:54.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A security patrol confronted him.

422
00:24:54.326 --> 00:24:56.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He told them he had
to provide for his family,

423
00:24:57.121 --> 00:24:59.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that he wasn't afraid of them.

424
00:24:59.206 --> 00:25:00.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There was a fight. He was killed.

425
00:25:03.085 --> 00:25:04.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

426
00:25:05.879 --> 00:25:08.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
After that, we came here.

427
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:11.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We thought we'd finally found a place
where no one would bother us.

428
00:25:11.927 --> 00:25:14.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe this time it'll be different.

429
00:25:15.472 --> 00:25:16.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe.

430
00:25:18.892 --> 00:25:20.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But even if it isn't...

431
00:25:22.104 --> 00:25:24.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
thank you for trying.

432
00:25:32.530 --> 00:25:34.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I should get
a good night's sleep,

433
00:25:34.532 --> 00:25:37.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I'm going to be my best
at the negotiations tomorrow.

434
00:25:44.668 --> 00:25:45.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, Neelix?

435
00:25:48.922 --> 00:25:51.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's been a wonderful day.

436
00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:04.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't there enough to mine here,
without destroying their home?

437
00:26:04.354 --> 00:26:08.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Their home contains more
than 30 percent of the field's ore.

438
00:26:08.692 --> 00:26:10.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Without that asteroid...

439
00:26:10.986 --> 00:26:13.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the operation isn't worth the expense.

440
00:26:15.115 --> 00:26:17.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you be open
to some kind of compensation?

441
00:26:18.327 --> 00:26:20.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All we want are the minerals.

442
00:26:20.871 --> 00:26:23.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you'd kill us to get them.

443
00:26:23.791 --> 00:26:25.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait.

444
00:26:25.626 --> 00:26:31.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Talaxians have found a way
to produce a lot of geothermal energy.

445
00:26:32.049 --> 00:26:33.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe they could share it with you.

446
00:26:36.303 --> 00:26:38.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you mean "share"?

447
00:26:40.474 --> 00:26:44.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could convert it into fuel
to power your ships.

448
00:26:45.813 --> 00:26:48.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The energy they generate isn't
compatible with our technology.

449
00:26:49.024 --> 00:26:51.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd be willing to help you
make the modifications.

450
00:26:51.652 --> 00:26:55.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have quotas to meet.
We don't have time for that.

451
00:26:55.697 --> 00:26:59.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, the future of more
than 500 people is at stake here.

452
00:27:04.748 --> 00:27:06.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And once, there was
a transporter accident.

453
00:27:07.084 --> 00:27:09.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix and Commander Tuvok
got combined

454
00:27:09.336 --> 00:27:11.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to make a completely different person.

455
00:27:11.171 --> 00:27:12.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

456
00:27:12.339 --> 00:27:15.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't think I could make up
a story like that, do you?

457
00:27:15.342 --> 00:27:17.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Neelix.

458
00:27:18.220 --> 00:27:21.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Do you want to play Kadis-Kot?
-Maybe later.

459
00:27:21.265 --> 00:27:23.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

460
00:27:33.026 --> 00:27:35.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew it wouldn't work.

461
00:27:35.404 --> 00:27:37.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We did get them
to make a small concession.

462
00:27:37.447 --> 00:27:38.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They've extended the deadline.

463
00:27:38.991 --> 00:27:41.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll have enough time
to dismantle your equipment.

464
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:44.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks, but there's too much
to take with us.

465
00:27:46.623 --> 00:27:49.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Janeway has agreed
to ferry all of you

466
00:27:49.251 --> 00:27:51.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and your supplies
to the nearest M-Class planet.

467
00:27:58.676 --> 00:28:00.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Brax.
We're going home.

468
00:28:00.637 --> 00:28:04.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why?
-We have to pack. Come on.

469
00:28:09.062 --> 00:28:12.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You said you were gonna help us.
-Brax.

470
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:31.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me?

471
00:28:32.502 --> 00:28:36.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've detected five warp-capable species
within two light-years of the planet

472
00:28:36.298 --> 00:28:38.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
where we're taking the Talaxians.

473
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:41.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm worried they might be
vulnerable to attack.

474
00:28:41.136 --> 00:28:44.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They would be vulnerable anywhere.
-I thought maybe you could help me

475
00:28:44.765 --> 00:28:47.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
devise some defense strategies
for their new home.

476
00:28:48.560 --> 00:28:52.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Frankly, Mr. Neelix, they don't seem
inclined to defend themselves.

477
00:28:52.314 --> 00:28:54.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, I suppose not...

478
00:28:54.566 --> 00:28:57.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But if they were going
to make a stand...

479
00:28:58.111 --> 00:29:00.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
their emotional attachment
to their present home

480
00:29:00.239 --> 00:29:01.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
might be an asset.

481
00:29:02.407 --> 00:29:05.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you saying they should stay?

482
00:29:05.577 --> 00:29:07.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm speaking hypothetically.

483
00:29:08.038 --> 00:29:09.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hypothetically...

484
00:29:10.499 --> 00:29:13.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if they wanted to defend the asteroid,
how would they do it?

485
00:29:15.337 --> 00:29:18.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To begin with, they would need
to establish some kind of perimeter.

486
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:22.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You mean shields?
-Yes.

487
00:29:22.344 --> 00:29:24.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The miners are monitoring
the asteroid.

488
00:29:25.013 --> 00:29:26.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If they detected the Talaxians
erecting a shield,

489
00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:28.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they would attempt to stop them.

490
00:29:29.977 --> 00:29:31.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose so.

491
00:29:31.979 --> 00:29:34.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your people would need competent
leadership to defend against

492
00:29:34.564 --> 00:29:36.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a preemptive attack.

493
00:29:37.776 --> 00:29:39.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you had the Captain's permission,

494
00:29:39.861 --> 00:29:41.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
would you be willing
to provide that leadership?

495
00:29:41.822 --> 00:29:43.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Certainly not.

496
00:29:43.907 --> 00:29:45.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It would be a violation
of the Prime Directive.

497
00:29:46.034 --> 00:29:47.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And even if it weren't,

498
00:29:47.828 --> 00:29:51.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't believe that I am the person
most qualified to assume that role.

499
00:29:54.751 --> 00:29:56.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You mean me?

500
00:29:56.295 --> 00:29:58.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am merely speaking hypothetically.

501
00:30:03.552 --> 00:30:06.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I couldn't lead those people,
Mr. Tuvok.

502
00:30:09.016 --> 00:30:10.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not a fighter.

503
00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:13.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just a cook...

504
00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:16.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who sometimes imagines himself
to be a diplomat.

505
00:30:16.732 --> 00:30:19.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On the contrary, Mr. Neelix...

506
00:30:20.819 --> 00:30:23.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you are much more than that.

507
00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:28.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are perhaps the most resourceful
individual I have ever known.

508
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:31.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I always thought you
just tolerated me.

509
00:30:32.956 --> 00:30:35.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You do have some annoying habits.

510
00:30:36.084 --> 00:30:39.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
However, during your time on<i> Voyager,</i>

511
00:30:39.421 --> 00:30:42.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you've developed many valuable skills.

512
00:30:42.424 --> 00:30:44.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Skills that would serve you well
if you ever decided

513
00:30:45.093 --> 00:30:47.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to assume a leadership role.

514
00:30:48.096 --> 00:30:49.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You really think so?

515
00:30:50.432 --> 00:30:52.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me be clear.

516
00:30:52.476 --> 00:30:55.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not urging you to do anything.

517
00:30:55.354 --> 00:30:59.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am simply telling you that I believe
that you are more than capable.

518
00:31:11.203 --> 00:31:13.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Going somewhere, Mr. Neelix?

519
00:31:13.455 --> 00:31:14.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just to see my friends.

520
00:31:14.623 --> 00:31:16.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chakotay tells me you're
using your own ship.

521
00:31:16.750 --> 00:31:18.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why not have Tom
take you in the <i>Flyer</i>?

522
00:31:18.627 --> 00:31:20.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I didn't want to bother anyone.

523
00:31:20.295 --> 00:31:23.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You wouldn't be planning
anything foolish, would you?

524
00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:26.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Whatever I do, I promise
it won't involve<i> Voyager.</i>

525
00:31:26.551 --> 00:31:28.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That wasn't my question.

526
00:31:29.638 --> 00:31:32.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know you have
Prime Directive issues,

527
00:31:32.974 --> 00:31:35.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'm not officially
part of your crew,

528
00:31:35.185 --> 00:31:36.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I don't have
the same constraints.

529
00:31:37.062 --> 00:31:39.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're as much a part of this crew
as anyone else.

530
00:31:41.024 --> 00:31:42.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you ordering me not to go?

531
00:31:42.442 --> 00:31:44.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That depends on what
you're going to do.

532
00:31:46.488 --> 00:31:48.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's up to the Talaxians.

533
00:31:57.749 --> 00:32:00.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Safe journey, Mr. Neelix.

534
00:32:09.886 --> 00:32:14.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know from personal experience
that you have force field emitters.

535
00:32:14.516 --> 00:32:17.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could use them
to establish a shield grid.

536
00:32:19.187 --> 00:32:21.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd need to deploy
a series of them

537
00:32:21.398 --> 00:32:25.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on the asteroid's surface,
along bisecting diameters.

538
00:32:25.444 --> 00:32:28.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
16 emitters should be enough
to form a grid.

539
00:32:28.363 --> 00:32:31.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even if you're right, it'd take weeks
to dig that many tunnels to the surface.

540
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:34.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander Tuvok suggested
that we could modify the emitters,

541
00:32:35.078 --> 00:32:38.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so they could be fired
from torpedo tubes on your ship...

542
00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:40.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
implanted in the surface.

543
00:32:41.668 --> 00:32:44.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As soon as the miners realize
what we are doing, they'd attack.

544
00:32:44.379 --> 00:32:46.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I could provide cover
from my ship.

545
00:32:46.465 --> 00:32:48.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you're right,
we'd have to work quickly.

546
00:32:48.341 --> 00:32:50.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could route power to the emitters
directly from the core.

547
00:32:51.094 --> 00:32:53.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They'd have a permanent energy supply.
-Good idea.

548
00:32:53.805 --> 00:32:56.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we do what you're suggesting,
people are going to be hurt.

549
00:32:56.475 --> 00:32:58.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is your home!

550
00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:04.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The miners have no right
to force you out.

551
00:33:04.483 --> 00:33:06.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I agree, but fighting?

552
00:33:06.610 --> 00:33:07.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't like it either,

553
00:33:08.028 --> 00:33:10.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but, at some point,
you have to stand up for yourselves.

554
00:33:10.697 --> 00:33:12.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How do you know
there won't be someone else

555
00:33:12.324 --> 00:33:14.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to terrorize you
the next place you go?!

556
00:33:14.910 --> 00:33:16.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[loud chatter]

557
00:33:16.411 --> 00:33:18.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know he's right.

558
00:33:21.082 --> 00:33:23.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No one has worked harder
to build this place than you.

559
00:33:24.628 --> 00:33:26.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn't it worth defending?

560
00:33:38.683 --> 00:33:40.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait for my comm call.

561
00:33:40.810 --> 00:33:44.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As soon as the last emitter's in place,
start routing power to the grid.

562
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:46.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Understood.

563
00:33:49.152 --> 00:33:50.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're scared, aren't you?

564
00:33:53.365 --> 00:33:55.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You?
-Terrified.

565
00:33:57.327 --> 00:33:59.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Be careful.
-I will.

566
00:33:59.955 --> 00:34:01.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[beeping]
<i>-Oxilon to Neelix.</i>

567
00:34:02.040 --> 00:34:04.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The emitters are loaded.</i>
<i>We're ready.</i>

568
00:34:05.961 --> 00:34:07.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll see you soon.

569
00:34:38.868 --> 00:34:41.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Two more, and we're done.
-[Oxilon]<i> Acknowledged.</i>

570
00:34:41.329 --> 00:34:43.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're moving into position
for the next one.

571
00:34:44.457 --> 00:34:47.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm sounds]

572
00:34:47.586 --> 00:34:49.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The miners' ship
is on an intercept course.

573
00:34:49.254 --> 00:34:50.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Evasive maneuvers!

574
00:34:56.761 --> 00:34:58.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They're targeting our shields.
-[Neelix]<i> I'll deal with them.</i>

575
00:34:59.097 --> 00:35:00.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just focus on your job.

576
00:35:02.225 --> 00:35:05.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All right, Mr. Vulcan, let's see
if you were right about me.

577
00:35:15.196 --> 00:35:17.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[loud chatter]
-[alarm sounds]

578
00:35:19.326 --> 00:35:20.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix, you have to hurry.

579
00:35:20.827 --> 00:35:23.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just one more emitter,
and you can activate the shield.

580
00:35:28.835 --> 00:35:30.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm sounds]

581
00:35:34.424 --> 00:35:35.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix to Oxilon.

582
00:35:35.634 --> 00:35:38.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-My weapons are off-line.</i>
-We're not in position yet.

583
00:35:38.345 --> 00:35:41.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You have to get there.</i>
<i>They're going to launch another charge.</i>

584
00:35:49.147 --> 00:35:51.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Neelix, what are you doing?
-[Neelix]<i> Don't worry about me.</i>

585
00:35:51.691 --> 00:35:54.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just get ready
to bring the grid online.

586
00:36:02.702 --> 00:36:05.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Delta Flyer </i>to Neelix.
Are you all right?

587
00:36:05.664 --> 00:36:08.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fine, Captain,
but you shouldn't be here.

588
00:36:08.792 --> 00:36:10.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You're violating the Prime Directive.</i>

589
00:36:10.877 --> 00:36:13.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're just helping a friend in distress.

590
00:36:29.312 --> 00:36:30.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dexa to Neelix.

591
00:36:31.147 --> 00:36:33.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The shield's holding. You did it.

592
00:36:34.567 --> 00:36:35.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We did it.

593
00:36:38.113 --> 00:36:41.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54868.6.</i>

594
00:36:42.158 --> 00:36:44.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Commander Nocona</i>
<i>seems to have given up</i>

595
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:47.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>his attempts to penetrate</i>
<i>the Talaxians' shield.</i>

596
00:36:47.288 --> 00:36:50.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Voyager's<i> ready to get underway,</i>
<i>but we're giving Mr. Neelix time</i>

597
00:36:50.375 --> 00:36:52.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to say a difficult good-bye</i>
<i>to his new friends.</i>

598
00:36:52.961 --> 00:36:55.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're grateful
for everything you've done.

599
00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:57.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just happy things worked out.

600
00:36:57.465 --> 00:37:00.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I'm glad that I could
spend some time here...

601
00:37:00.885 --> 00:37:01.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with all of you.

602
00:37:03.722 --> 00:37:05.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'd better go.
-Stay here!

603
00:37:05.974 --> 00:37:07.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He can't, Brax.

604
00:37:08.351 --> 00:37:10.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He has responsibilities on<i> Voyager.</i>

605
00:37:10.729 --> 00:37:13.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I promise I'll stay in touch
as long as I can.

606
00:37:34.544 --> 00:37:36.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[door chimes]
-Come in.

607
00:37:41.342 --> 00:37:42.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hi.

608
00:37:43.344 --> 00:37:44.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neelix!

609
00:37:47.682 --> 00:37:49.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you working on?

610
00:37:50.185 --> 00:37:52.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A report on proto-humanoid cultures...

611
00:37:52.937 --> 00:37:55.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for Commander Chakotay's
paleontology class.

612
00:37:56.983 --> 00:37:59.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A-ha. Need some help?

613
00:37:59.944 --> 00:38:01.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm almost finished.

614
00:38:01.738 --> 00:38:02.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

615
00:38:03.948 --> 00:38:05.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have time
for a game of Kadis-Kot?

616
00:38:06.659 --> 00:38:08.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have to get up early.

617
00:38:09.037 --> 00:38:10.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

618
00:38:10.955 --> 00:38:12.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess you'd better
get to sleep then.

619
00:38:15.335 --> 00:38:17.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you want me to tuck you in?
Tell you a bedtime story?

620
00:38:19.297 --> 00:38:20.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[scoffs]
You haven't done that in years.

621
00:38:23.051 --> 00:38:25.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just think of all the stories
you've missed.

622
00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:28.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks, Neelix,
but I can put myself to bed.

623
00:38:30.225 --> 00:38:32.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not a little girl anymore.

624
00:38:48.535 --> 00:38:51.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't think anyone else
stayed up this late.

625
00:38:53.498 --> 00:38:57.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I wouldn't want you
to have coffee all by yourself.

626
00:38:58.169 --> 00:38:59.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have a seat.

627
00:39:03.091 --> 00:39:04.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

628
00:39:09.055 --> 00:39:11.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've been thinking about something.

629
00:39:13.601 --> 00:39:15.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a little hard to put into words.

630
00:39:16.563 --> 00:39:19.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I haven't really made
a decision yet.

631
00:39:19.941 --> 00:39:23.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, of course, I would never ignore
my responsibilities on<i> Voyager.</i>

632
00:39:23.987 --> 00:39:25.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course not.

633
00:39:25.780 --> 00:39:27.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I take them very seriously.

634
00:39:27.991 --> 00:39:29.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know you do.

635
00:39:33.872 --> 00:39:37.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been thinking about something, too.
Maybe you could help me.

636
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:40.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be happy to.

637
00:39:42.213 --> 00:39:45.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's an idea I'd need to talk
to Starfleet Command about.

638
00:39:46.968 --> 00:39:49.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It must be important.
-It is.

639
00:39:50.972 --> 00:39:54.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now that we've established
two-way communication with Earth...

640
00:39:56.561 --> 00:39:59.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it seems to me Starfleet could use
a permanent ambassador

641
00:39:59.981 --> 00:40:01.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Delta Quadrant.

642
00:40:02.567 --> 00:40:06.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This ambassador would have to stay
in frequent contact with<i> Voyager.</i>

643
00:40:07.363 --> 00:40:08.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[quietly]
Certainly.

644
00:40:11.409 --> 00:40:15.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It would be difficult for me
to run this ship without you, Neelix.

645
00:40:17.081 --> 00:40:20.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But that might be a sacrifice
I'd be willing to make...

646
00:40:20.710 --> 00:40:22.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for the greater good of Starfleet.

647
00:40:24.589 --> 00:40:27.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course, the assignment
would be entirely voluntary.

648
00:40:31.429 --> 00:40:34.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wouldn't be interested, would you?

649
00:41:42.959 --> 00:41:44.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good-bye...

650
00:41:45.336 --> 00:41:47.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and good luck, Ambassador.

651
00:41:59.934 --> 00:42:00.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Neelix.

652
00:42:12.572 --> 00:42:15.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Live long and prosper.

653
00:42:36.012 --> 00:42:37.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

654
00:43:01.245 --> 00:43:02.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

